(70, 49, NULL, 'txteditor', '<p>Market research includes accumulation of information/data to understand more about targeted demographics and consumers. It enables businesses to market effectively and carve a niche in the market. Market research is a crucial element of any business strategy, whether it is a Business-to-Business (B2B) or Business-to-Customer (B2C), irrespective of the business size and age.&nbsp;</p><p>It offers answers to the companies to make decisions based on the information. Whether a business is looking forward to emerging market trends, identifying core customer behavioral patterns or devising a marketing strategy; the answer to all is - Market Research. The benefits of market research are highlighted below:</p><p><strong>●	Maintain a customer-focussed approach -</strong> Market research allows the businesses to understand the needs and demands of the customers, inclusive of other aspects of targeted customers. A business cannot build an effective customer-centric approach without understanding customer pain-points and preferences.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>●	Establish more effective connection with the audiences -</strong> When a business identifies and understands its target customers better, it can effectively reach them. Marketers don\'t have to waste time and finances on trial-and-error, as an informed marketing strategy can be devised. Market research helps in acquiring all the data pertaining to the market.</p><p><strong>●	Unleashes growth opportunities -</strong> Market research is imperative for new companies or existing ones intending to launch new products into the market. Conducting periodic market research helps to unleash new opportunities to grow and improve.</p><p><strong>●	Risk Mitigation -</strong> Any business comes with a risk. And because of the high risk involved in developing a product without prior research, market research helps to predict whether or not a product concept has actual potential for success. And will the product meet the customer expectations? Without optimum market research, risks tend to be higher.</p><p><strong>●	Make sound decisions -</strong> Market research bestows autonomy on a company to arrive at a sound decision backed by profound information and not just gut feelings. Gut feelings are not trust-worthy means of making decisions.&nbsp;</p><p>Market research can serve as solid data to take a company closer to its objectives and successfully convert the potential customers and retain the existing ones.</p><p><strong>●	Attain competitive-edge -</strong> Robust market research can offer a competitive edge to the businesses in the marketplace. To top it up, market research also gives information and deeper insights about the competitors and understand how effectively a business can accommodate in the market.</p><p><strong>●	Stay at the fore-front of emerging trends -</strong> Market research allows businesses to stay at the top of the emerging trends in the market. In today\'s time, market culture tends to be volatile and market research is has to be in sync with the ongoing trends.</p><p>Without thorough market research, marketing objectives of a business would remain unrequited.</p><p><br></p>', NULL),
(71, 50, NULL, 'txteditor', '<p>Your site is vital for your advertising methodology. It delivers the first impression to your&nbsp;targeting audience, affecting your customer’s experience in numerous ways. At the point when&nbsp;your customer searches for a solution, a wonderfully designed and optimized site will catch their&nbsp;attention and offer your item the consideration it deserves.</p><p><strong>4 Ways your target audience is impacted by your web design</strong></p><p>They are urgent angles that sway the customer experience your crowd will have and impact the&nbsp;navigability, the loading speed, the worth, the activities, and the trust connection between you &amp;&nbsp;your customers.</p><p><strong>1. Content</strong></p><p>Content is king. At the point when a guest arrives at your site, they need to comprehend what&nbsp;your business does for sure assistance you offer initially - the fact that guests don\'t peruse the&nbsp;site, they examine it - to choose if they have any desire to stay and observe what they are&nbsp;looking, or leave.</p><p>The content should be succinct, obviously making sense of what you do and why they ought to&nbsp;work with you. An expert web specialist will actually want to arrange your business thoughts,&nbsp;editing, and writing with instinctive and familiar navigation styles to assist the guests to find the&nbsp;data they need.</p><p><strong>2. Appearance</strong></p><p>On the off chance that you are in a rush to find a solution for an issue, what might you like: to&nbsp;puzzle through a labyrinth of sections and ways or quickly find the answer at maximum capacity&nbsp;before you?</p><p>The effect of your site\'s appearance will assume a full part in your first impression on new&nbsp;visitors or support your ability to older customers. Consequently, regardless of which style you&nbsp;pick, the appearance should be appealing and modern with forward-thinking, current design&nbsp;trends.</p><p><strong>3. Functionality</strong></p><p>Your site is for your clients. Your site isn\'t working for yourself; it is working for your target&nbsp;audience. Just and first, for them. It requires work such that your audience will actually want to&nbsp;explore and understand.</p><p><strong>4. Professionalism</strong></p><p>The impression you make on your site\'s guests is sooner than they begin reading your site. The&nbsp;configuration your site is introduced to shows the way in which proficient and decent you are.&nbsp;They show how much you value your customers and how you need to be seen by them. Your&nbsp;clients will perceive the way you esteem them through pages such as About Us, Professional&nbsp;Staff Photos, Customer Results, Testimonials, and so forth.</p>', NULL),
(72, 51, NULL, 'txteditor', '<p>From thousands of distinct crypto-currencies, it could be overwhelming for the ones stepping into the space of crypto-currencies as an amateur. Based on the market capitalisation, here are some of the best crypto-currencies to invest in 2022:</p><p><strong>●	BTC (Bitcoin) -</strong> With a market capital of 846 billion dollars, Bitcoin was developed in 2009 by Santoshi Nakamoto and is the original crypto-currency. Similar to a majority of crypto-currencies, BTC runs on a blockchain platform.&nbsp;</p><p>By deploying a process called \'proof of work\' that involves solving crypto puzzles, the currency is kept secure and protected from fraudsters. The Bitcoin price had exponentially increased from 500 dollars in 2016 to 44,000 dollars as of March 1, 2022, indicating a rise of 7800%.</p><p><strong>●	ETH (Ethereum) -</strong> Having a market capital of over 361 billion dollars, ETH is both a crypto-currency and blockchain interface. The currency is quite popular amongst software developers because of its potential functions such as smart contracts that include automated execution as conditions are met and unique digital identifiers.&nbsp;</p><p>In April 2011, the currency was priced at 11 dollars and has grown to 3000 dollars by the start of March, registering an increase of 27,000%.</p><p><strong>●	BNB (Binance Coin) -</strong> With a market capital of over 68 billion dollars, Binance was launched in 2017. This currency was used for trading and paying fees on Binance crypto-exchange, one of the largest across the globe.&nbsp;</p><p>BNB can also be used for trading and exchanging other forms of crypto-currency, such as ETH or BTC. The price of BNB in 2017 was 0.10 dollars and by the beginning of March grew to about 413 dollars, inflating by about 4,10,000%.</p><p><strong>●	XRP -</strong> With a market capital of more than 37 billion dollars, XRP is a payment processing and digital technology company. The currency can be used to encourage exchange of various currency types (including major crypto-currencies and fiat currencies).&nbsp;</p><p>At the start of 2017, the price of XRP was 0.006 dollars. And by March 2022, it climbed to 0.80 dollars accounting for a rise of more than 12,600%.</p><p><strong>●	LTC (Litecoin) -</strong> Owning a market capital of over 9 billion dollars, LTC is an open-source blockchain crypto-curreny launched in 2011. It was developed by Charlie Lee, a former crypto-exchange software developer. LTC is one of the crypto-currencies whose code is copied from BTC. It is designed to have a speedy transaction time.&nbsp;</p><p>It can be used as a platform for making payments to people across the globe without an intermediary. The token value of LTC is 106 dollars and is the 21st largest crypto-currency in the world.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Find the crypto-currency of your choice and start investing!</strong></p><p><br></p>', NULL),
(73, 52, NULL, 'txteditor', '<p>DNS protection gives an extra layer of protection between a worker and the internet by&nbsp;blacklisting hazardous websites and sifting through undesirable content. By utilizing&nbsp;secure DNS servers both at home and at work, representatives can keep away from&nbsp;unnecessary dangers and the potential for malicious attacks.</p><p><strong>How does DNS Protection work?</strong></p><p>Consider DNS a telephone directory, yet rather than planning individuals\' names to their&nbsp;street address, the telephone directory maps PC names to IP addresses. Each planning&nbsp;is known as a \"DNS record.\"</p><p>The internet has a lot of PCs, so it doesn\'t seem OK to place every one of the records in&nbsp;one major book. All things considered, DNS is organized into more modest books or&nbsp;domains. domains can be exceptionally huge, so they are additionally organized into&nbsp;more modest books, called, \"zones.\"</p><p>All things being equal, there are several DNS servers that store all the DNS records for&nbsp;the internet. Any PC that needs to realize a number or a name can ask their DNS&nbsp;server, and their DNS server knows how to ask - or question - other DNS servers when&nbsp;they need a record. At the point when a DNS server questions other DNS servers, it\'s&nbsp;making an \"upstream\" inquiry. Inquiries for a domain can go \"upstream\" until they lead&nbsp;back to the domain’s authority, or \"definitive name server.\"</p><p>A definitive name server is a place where administrators oversee server names and IP&nbsp;addresses for their domains. Whenever a DNS executive needs to add, change or&nbsp;erase a server name or an IP address, they roll out an improvement on their&nbsp;authoritative DNS server.</p><p><strong>Why is DNS Protection Important?</strong></p><p>DNS protection can assist you with getting both home and corporate organizations.&nbsp;Secure DNS solutions can be a good choice to upgrade BYOD approaches and&nbsp;safeguard information inside and outside the workstation.</p><p>DNS protection has the accompanying abilities:</p><p><strong>Phishing &amp; Malware Protection</strong></p><p>This ability locks out sites containing malicious risky content such as scams and&nbsp;viruses. The most ideal way to avoid these sorts of attacks is to take on a content&nbsp;filtering solution and educate staff about these risks.</p><p><strong>Ad-Blocking</strong></p><p>This is an essential part of the content filtering abilities that is used to block&nbsp;advertisements that endeavor to gather vital information from staff.</p><p><strong>Better Speeds</strong></p><p>Further developing your system speeds can make you more proficient and enhance&nbsp;overall productivity. More often than not, protected DNS servers offer quicker lookups&nbsp;than those presented by service providers.</p>', NULL),
